<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-280-045 </DOCNO><DOCID>07 444 456</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Desktop Publishing  July 3 1989 v3 n11 p1(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Grammar checkers: how good are they?andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT/><TEXT>WRITING AIDS have entered a new era with the advent of grammar and stylecheckers-programs that purport to correct poorly written prose and to guideauthors toward a writing style that is matched to the intellectual grasp andtaste of the intended reader.andP;  In a look at six grammar/style checkersavailable for PCs or Macs, we found that experienced editors, with practice,will indeed find these usefull.andP;  But they still are no substitute forlearning grammar the hard way.andO;</TEXT></DOC>